  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7047.94 sitting just below the massive 7050 gamma wall (13.4B), dealers are aggressively selling into this bounce as they hedge their long gamma position. The PIN regime is functioning as expected with dealers providing liquidity against the move, but the wall_break event suggests we've likely breached a key support level on the downside. Watch 7000 as the next major support with 8.2B in positive gamma, while any push back toward 7050 will face heavy dealer selling pressure.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect dealers to cap rallies near 7050 and provide support around 7000, keeping price range-bound.",
